Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Defendant Earnest Princeton Love in court.  Attorney Michael J Steinle in court for Earnest Princeton Love.  Prosecuting attorney Nate Kristian McClure in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.
AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2:
Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Complaint/Information.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement received, signed and filed.
 
Court ordered case adjourned for Review in Branch 17.
Review hearing scheduled for November 15, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Earnest Princeton Love in court with attorney Michael J Steinle.  Jon R Josephsen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.
